  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, when we come into the forest ourself, when we came closer up toward the city of Hornbaek, we see the bright lights on the brakes of this bus.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And once we saw it stopped, we knew something was wrong, because the bus never stopped there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what it was-- and we had been sold out by my uncle's friend next door.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't know that he was a Nazi sympathizer, even though they had been friends with him for 25 years.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And for $5, I think, something like $5 apiece, we were sold out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And how we found out afterwards was that my friend went to the bus driver when we saw the bus had come into the city of Hornbaek and nobody was there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he said that the Germans had boarded the bus.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they stood with a list with seven names on and read it off.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they took my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And all-- they took the four people that were on the bus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But they knew specifically who they were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So when they asked for the names, and they said, yes, that's me and, yes, it's me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course, they said, please, step out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they had to step out of the bus.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that we had seen the stop, we figured something was, like I said, something was wrong.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we said, let's get the hell out of here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think that with the speed of bicycles to [INAUDIBLE] forest and  upper back road, and around the whole back way, it's like another 6 miles around till you can go a back road and then come into the city on the back side and then to the friend's house.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
